cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning model for segmenting contusions and lesions from brain MRI images of patients with TBI. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed model is a convolutional neural network (CNN), which is a type of deep learning algorithm commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, sub-categories related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) are also likely. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
